description:
Life takes a turn for the fantastic when the enigmatic Dr. Riddles and his puppet-like partner, Kedo the mamodo, pop into town. Armed with an arsenal of baffling tricks and traps, Dr. Riddles forces Kiyo to question the very nature of his knowledge about both Zatch and his book. Do Zatch and Kiyo have enough strength to solve the doc's puzzles and learn a new spell at the same time?

Awaken The Power Inside!

Newly arrived in the jungles of South America, Kiyo, Zatch and their friends dive into battle with Milordo-Z's cabal of revived 1,000-year-old mamodo. Though these ancient warriors boast frightening powers and spells, Zatch and Kanchom are reluctant to do harm to the mamodo and their brainwashed book owners. After all, it's the fiendish Milordo-Z's fault that they're even here in the first place. Can Zatch be victorious if he keeps holding back? And what's this? Will Ponygon finally find a partner?

Awaken The Power Inside!

During the course of their many battles, Zatch and Kiyo have chanced upon several mysterious stone tablets that closely resemble mamodo. As it turns out, during the last fight to determine the king of the mamodo 1,000 years ago, one mamodo had the power to freeze his competition in suspended animation. Now, someone has discovered a way to reanimate these stone tablets, and that spells mega-trouble for Kiyo and Zatch, especially since they're now terribly outnumbered!

Old friends Li-En and Dr. Riddles arrive with their mamodo to provide backup, but are they too late to help?

Will Parco and his timid companion pull off the showstopper to end all showstoppers, or has their luck finally run out? With a little help from the mysterious Dr. Riddles, they just might stay in the running to be king.

Now that the ultra-powerful Brago and his partner Sherry have confronted the diabolical Zofis, Zatch and his gang head off in search of teh elusive "moonlight"--the supernatural power source that fuels Zofis's army. Meanwhile, Sherry and Brago's emotional battle against Koko and Zofis is reaching its climax.

Momon is a somewhat cowardly character who's been able to avoid competing in the battle to become king thanks to his radar-like abilities that allow him to pinpoint other mamodo's locations. But when he uses his skills to catch the ever-ready-to-strangle-someone Tia off guard, he risks earning himself a fast trip to the hospital. What's a naughty bunny in the big city to do?

Keith has vowed to finish the fight before his stogie is done, and now Kanchom's only hope for survival rests on a new spell that has the potential to literally multiply his power. The mighty Faudo, a mamodo bigger than a mountain, has come to life...and he's on his way to destroy Japan! Inside the monster's innards, Zatch and his friends fight Riou, the evil mamodo who controls the behemoth. Can they stop him in time, or is Tokyo doomed? Who will be the master of monsters?

Having uncovered the dark secret of her enigmatic classmate, Edward Cullen, Bella Swan embraces her feelings for him, trusting Edward to keep her safe despite the risks. When a rival clan of vampires makes its way into Forks, though, the danger to Bella has never been more real. Will she make the ultimate sacrifice to protect the people dearest to her?

Alter Ego proudly presents 'Tales from the Code!' The coming of the Comics Code Authority in 1954-55 changed comics greatly - and we document that process with comic art and script 'Before' and 'After' the CCA got hold of them, with art by Simon & Kirby, Ditko, Buscema, Sinnott, Gould, Cole, Steranko, Krigstein, O'Neill, Glanzman, Orlando, Williamson, Heath, and many others! Featuring a fabulous new Spider-Man cover by Josh Medors!

description: After being named People Magazine's Sexiest Man Alive and starring in the upcoming Summer Blockbuster, Green Lantern, Ryan Reynolds has many brightest days ahead of him. From leaving his home in Canada to conquering the big screen in Hollywood, take a look at the life of one of acting's hottest stars. With his roles in romantic comedies to action turns as some of comics' most beloved characters, Ryan Reynolds is proving himself a force at the box office.
name: Fame: Ryan Reynolds

description: A reprint of Legion of Super-Heroes Annual #1 "Revenge is a Dish Best Served Cold" under the new series name of "Tales of the Legion of Super-Heroes" (issues 314-354) but continued the numbering from the last series titled The Legion of Super-Heroes (issues 259-313). As a result even though this issue in essence is #1 in the volume, the numbering starts at #4.
name: Revenge Is a Dish Best Served Cold

description: The too-crazy-not-to-be-true story of the comic book industry ends at new beginnings! GRAPHIC NOVELS: Where did the term come from -- Will Eisner, or a Swiss artist who died a century before he was born? The unbelievable biography of Osamu Tezuka, GOD OF MANGA, and how he led Japanese comics to dominance on both sides of the Pacific! And finally, the DIRECT MARKET, and how it led to a creative revolution in comics -- economic challenges -- and can it survive the threat from DIGITAL PIRACY?
name: Comics of the Future
